						<summary>

						<p>An image lying under baniyan tree in survey No. 111/A, to the east of the village.</p>						

						<p>14th century A.D.</p>						

						<p>This undated inscription may be assigned to 14th century A.D. on palaeography grounds.</p>						

						<p>It mentions certain Mōli Tikkanāyakuḍu <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Periya Perumāladāsu. The image contains figure of a person with folded hands probably refers to the person mentioned in the epigraph.</p>						

						</summary>
